-- Treasury’s Lew Convenes Financial Stability Council Meeting
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2013-04-04T20:15:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-04/treasury-s-lew-convenes-financial-stability-council-meeting.html
The Financial Stability Oversight
Council today discussed and “furthered its analysis” of non-
bank financial companies that are being considered to be
designated systemically important, the U.S. Treasury Department
said.  Treasury Secretary Jacob J. Lew, the council’s chairman,
led the meeting at the Treasury Department in  Washington ,
spokeswoman Suzanne Elio said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in Washington at 
